        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 1:37PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 137 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pontotoc, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Endville, Cherry Creek, Branyan, Chiwapa, Algoma, Plantersville, Jug
Fork, Trace State Park, Sherman, Flowerdale, Rough Edge, Nixon, Beech
Springs, Skyline, Pontotoc, Belden, Tupelo, Palmetto, Bissell, and
Birmingham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
